<HEADLINE> Philippines to Buy Fighters, Patrol Vessels: Officer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Armed Forces of the
Philippines (AFP) will buy 12 multi-role fighters (MRF) and three
offshore patrol vessels (OPV) as part of its 15-year modernization
program.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed Monday by two officers of the Philippine Air
Force and the Philippine Navy during a briefing here for
representatives of the proponents for the fighters and patrol
vessels, according to the official Philippine News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Col. Rodante Joya, chairman of the MRF's Bids, Acquisition and
Negotiations Committee, said the air force needs 12 MRFs,
including nine single-seat and three dual-seat.
</P>
<P>
Commodore Ruben Espejo, chief negotiator for OPV procurement,
said three OPVs will be purchased in the first phase of the first
five-year period of the AFP modernization program, which has been
earmarked by the congress with a total of 332 billion pesos (8.5
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
In the second phase of the first five-year period, 12 more MRFs
and four more OPVs will be purchased by the AFP. 
</P>
</TEXT>
