<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Mayor Vows To Improve Investment Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Mayor Jia Qinglin today
pledged that substantial measures will be taken to improve the
local investment environment, so as to attract more international
companies to invest in the city.
</P>
<P>
Jia made the pledge at a discussion with resident
representatives of some 20 foreign companies here.
</P>
<P>
He told the foreign representatives that the city government
has worked out preferential policies for overseas investors in
hi-tech industries. In future, the city will work out more policies
to encourage investment from overseas, he said.
</P>
<P>
The city government will be streamlined, and will try to stop
illegal levying of funds on foreign-funded projects, he
said. Efforts will also be made to improve the environment, and
build more roads and subways.
</P>
<P>
Jia went on to say that the city government will study the
proposals by the representatives to allow overseas companies to
become involved in the fields of exports and imports, tourism,
accountancy and lawyers' services.
</P>
<P>
According to official figures, by the end of March this year
136 international companies had invested in 418 projects in
Beijing, involving total contractual foreign capital of 3.51
billion US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
