<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, April 27 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian Prime Minister Sergei Kiriyenko will cut the
administrative staff as the first step to streamline the bloated
government, a senior Russian official said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Alexander Kotenkov, the Russian president's representative in
the State Duma (Russia's lower house of parliament), said at a
press conference that the presidential administration will be cut
by 300 people.
</P>
<P>
He said the Russian Security Council has already laid off 100
employees. (Russia-Government)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- A total of 21 people were killed Sunday night by a
group of unidentified assailants in a border village called Mohra
Seiri in Mirpur Division of Pakistan-held Kashmir area.
</P>
<P>
According to a report Monday by the Associated Press of
Pakistan, the 21 people killed were from two families.
</P>
<P>
The report said some unidentified armed men entered the houses
of the two families in Mohra Seiri village near the line of
control in the Samanni Valley of Bhimber District in Mirpur
Division at around 11:15 p.m. Sunday night and gunned down 21
people including women and children.
</P>
<P>
Investigation of the incident is now under way.
(Pakistan-Killing)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
HANOI -- Nguyen Van Linh, former general secretary of the
Vietnamese Communist Party, died on Monday at the age of 82 in
southern Ho Chi Minh City, a communique said.
</P>
<P>
The communique was issued by the central committee of the
Communist Party of Vietnam (CPV), the president of Vietnam, the
National Assembly of Vietnam, the Vietnamese government, the
Vietnam Fatherland Front and the military central committee of the
CPV.
</P>
<P>
The communique said Linh "had made a great contribution to the
revolutionary cause of the CPV and the nation in his 70-year
revolutionary career," and that "his death was a great loss to the
CPV, the country and the people."
</P>
<P>
A state funeral will be held on April 29. Vietnam's national
flag will fly at half mast on April 28 and 29, and entertainment
has been forbidden, according to the CPV. (Vietnam-Former
Party Leader-Death)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOGADISHU -- Fighting around the Southern port of Kismayu in
Somalia seems to be escalating as the armed clashes enter the
fourth day Monday, spreading to territories controlled by the
faction led by Hussein Mohamed Aidid in Lower Jubba region.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest reports, the Majerten Militiamen led by
the son-in-law of Somalia's late dictator, General Mohamed Said
Hirsi Morgan, have been repulsed back for a few kilometers for the
first time since they launched what is seen as a decisive campaign
in eradicating the Marehan militiamen from the region.
</P>
<P>
Reports from Jilib District, 170 km North of Kismayu, indicate
that Colonel Abdullahi Garamgaram, the operation commander and a
well known military official among General Morgan's militia
leaders has been one of the deceased in Sunday's fighting around
the strategic village of Mugambo, 100 km North of Kismayu.
</P>
<P>
More than 50 people have so far been killed and nearly 70
others were wounded since the fighting has intensified four days
ago. (Somalia-Clan Fighting) 
</P>
</TEXT>
