<HEADLINE> 1 Turkish Soldier Killed in Land Mine Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- One soldier of the Turkish
government security forces was killed and eight others injured
Monday in a land mine blast in Hatay province bordering Syria, the
semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that a military vehicle hit the land mine in
Dortyol town Monday morning when it was on its way back from a
military operation against the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party
(PKK) rebels.
</P>
<P>
The wounded soldiers have been taken to hospital, and four of
them were in serious condition, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
The PKK militants, who have been fighting a separatist war
since August 1984, often cross into eastern and southeastern
Turkey from neighboring countries where they were hiding, to
attack military and civilian targets there.



27/04/98 16:26 GMT

NNNN
00:33 00:33 g # PAB
