<HEADLINE> Nepali PM Takes New Measures to Fight Corruption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Prime Minister Girija
Prasad Koirala on Monday directed secretaries of the government to
cooperate in making the administration impartial, clean,
transparent, economical and effective, the official RSS news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Koirala instructed the secretaries to cut down unnecessary and
unproductive expenditures, check dilly-dallying and ostentatious
behavior of offices and maintain financial discipline in an effort
to weed out corruption.
</P>
<P>
He said that as long as production is not raised, facilities
for employees cannot be increased, but increase in production
requires dedication and honesty on the part of the employees.
</P>
<P>
He called on the secretaries to hammer out separate
implementation plans and work accordingly.
</P>
<P>
On April 15, Koirala and his cabinet adopted a number of
decisions with a view to bringing under control the soaring
governmental expenditures and strictly implementing a policy of
financial discipline and austerity.
</P>
<P>
After taking office on April 15, Koirala promised to fight
rampant corruption in his country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
