<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-27 16:57 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus Bans Foreigner Construction Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Cypriot Interior Minister Dinos
Michaelides announced on Monday that Cyprus has decided to impose
a ban on foreign workers in the construction sector.
</P>
<P>
A ministerial committee on foreign workers in Cyprus made the
decision at a meeting during the day, Michaelides told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus will indefinitely stop issuing work permits or renewing
existing permits for foreign workers in the sector, he said,
adding that it will soon take the same measures in other sectors.
</P>
<P>
He said the move was prompted by the increased unemployment
rate, which stands at about 3 percent in recent years, on the
Mediterranean island.
</P>
<P>
There are some 1,000 foreigners currently employed in the
construction sector, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
He called on trade unions to help the government combat illegal
employment of foreign workers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
