<HEADLINE> Chinese General Calls on Indian Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 27 (Xinhua) -- General Fu Quanyou, chief of
general staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army, called on
Indian Prime Minister Atal Behari Vajpayee here Monday evening and
both sides expressed the desire to enhance the two countries'
ties.
</P>
<P>
After recalling his visit to China in 1979 when he was serving
as the Indian foreign minister, Vajpayee expressed his thanks to
Chinese leaders for their congratulatory messages when he was
sworn in as India's new prime minister last month, a member of
General Fu's entourage said.
</P>
<P>
Vajpayee said he shared the happiness of the Chinese people
over their achievements in the past few years and was satisfied
with the development of friendly relations between India and
China.
</P>
<P>
He said it takes time and patience to solve the border issue
between the two countries. What is more important is that the two
great countries are duty-bound to maintain regional and world
peace in face of the changes in the world situation.
</P>
<P>
General Fu said at the meeting that establishing long-term and
good-neighborly relations between China and India is not only in
the interests of the two countries and peoples, but also conducive
to regional and world peace and stability. He said the main
purpose of his current visit is to further promote Sino-Indian
friendly relations.
</P>
<P>
General Fu arrived here Sunday evening for a five-day official
visit to India. 
</P>
