<HEADLINE> Cyprus Removed From High Risk Money Laundering List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Cypriot Finance Minister
Christodoulos Christodoulou announced on Monday that his country
has been removed from the list of high risk money laundering
countries.
</P>
<P>
The minister said this was done by a committee of the Council
of Europe (CoE) monitoring efforts in combating money laundering
in member countries.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after meeting with representatives from
21 CoE members, Christodoulou said Cyprus' endeavor in this regard
has been evaluated by the Financial Action Task Force of CoE.
</P>
<P>
The Cypriot minister said Cyprus has ratified the international
convention of Vienna and the CoE convention, set up a special team
to fight money laundering and a consultative commission to inform
and assist the government about the issue.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus is the second country the CoE committee has visited,
after Slovenia. Christodoulou said the committee should visit all
member countries to see for itself practical steps each country is
taking to combat the crime. 
</P>
</TEXT>
