<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-27 17:56 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> KSE Index Up After Government Supporting Effort </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Kuwait Stock Exchange
(KSE) market index was up 58 points to close at 2206.5 points
Monday, the third straight day of rallying.
</P>
<P>
All KSE listed shares were on the rise, except for some but
mostly Arab banking institute shares. The gross rise for the three
days starting Saturday is 124.2 points.
</P>
<P>
Traded shares totaled 33.7 million Kuwait Dinars (111.21
million U.S. dollars) in value through 3,386 transactions Monday.
</P>
<P>
The rise followed a protracted retreat totaling 570.5 points
since the start of this year. The market was reacting quickly to a
government effort to support the mechanism of KSE.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti cabinet on Sunday reviewed a report on KSE activities
and decided to form a committee grouping the finance minister and
representatives of KSE and the Central Bank to recommend on how to
support the stock exchange and upgrade its role in supporting the
national economy. 
</P>
