<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Finalizes Mereb Basin Development Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The draft study on the Mereb
Basin Integrated Development Master Plan has been finalized, the
Ethiopian News Agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, an eight-day meeting appraising the
study was opened in Addis Ababa Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 400-km-long Mereb River is located in northern Ethiopia
and neighboring Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
The basin covers a total area of 23,932 square kms of which
5,900 square kms lies in Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the meeting, Project Manager Hamere Woundimu said
that the Ethiopian government has earmarked 2.36 million Birr
(342,000 U.S. Dollars) for the project which aims at identifying
natural resources available in the basin in kind and quantity.
</P>
<P>
The study also explores the potential of the basin for
irrigation, potable water, hydro-electric power generation and
mining, the manager added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
