<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-27 19:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Accused of Damaging PNA Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 27 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) accused Israel on Monday of damaging its economy
by obstructing free movement of Palestinian goods.
</P>
<P>
The Jerusalem-based Palestinian press service JMCC quoted PNA
Minister of Trade and Economy Maher Masri as saying that the way
the Palestinian goods is handled at the Karni crossing point is
back-to-back checking by the Israeli security forces.
</P>
<P>
The crossing point is between the Palestinian self-rule Gaza
Strip and Israel.
</P>
<P>
"Palestinian goods are unloaded onto the ground, undergo a
thorough security search and are then reloaded onto trucks, taking
a great deal of time for checking and causing a great deal of
spoilage," Masri said.
</P>
<P>
Israel has violated the 1994 Paris Economic Protocol, which
views the Palestinian area as a single geographic entity, he said.
</P>
<P>
Under the protocol, free movement of goods should be secured in
the Palestinian area, between the area and Israel as well as other
countries of the world, Masir said.
</P>
<P>
The protocol stipulates that the PNA has the sole authority
over goods passing all crossing points, but Israel is enforcing
security measures and has resulted in a decline of Palestinian
export to the Jewish state, he added.
</P>
<P>
Israel intends to deal a blow to the Palestinian economy by
allowing free flow of goods from Israel to Gaza, but obstructing
Palestinian goods from flowing into Israel, Gaza Governor Mohamed
Qudweh told JMCC.
</P>
<P>
According to a report issued on Monday by PNA Ministry of Trade
and Economy, Israel's imports from the Palestinian area has been
reduced sharply.
</P>
<P>
Israel exports about 3 billion U.S. dollars worth of goods
annually to the Palestinians, while the Palestinian export to
Israel stands at 300 million dollars in a year, the report said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
