<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Leone Celebrates Independence Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Sierra Leonean President Ahmed
Tejan Kabbah Monday called on the people of the country to work
together to build a better independent Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
In what was described as a "very strong" speech on the State
Radio to mark the country's 37th anniversary of independence,
President Kabbah congratulated Sierra Leoneans for their change
of attitude toward national issues.
</P>
<P>
Sierra Leone, a tiny west African country known for its rich
natural resources like diamond, gold and other minerals, won its
independence from Britain on April 27, 1961.
</P>
<P>
However, after 37 years, it seems a difficult job for Sierra
Leoneans to get much to celebrate the anniversary, especially as
the seven-year civil war has left the country in chaos, according
to a British Broadcasting Corporation report monitored here.
</P>
<P>
President Kabbah had to take Sierra Leoneans back to the days
when hospital provided medicines to the sick and poor, and the
police, the army and the civil service were considered the best
in west Africa.
</P>
<P>
According to what the president said, Sierra Leone was ahead
of such countries as Singapore and Malaysia in 1961. But today
it has been declared by the United Nations as one of the least
developed countries.
</P>
<P>
At independence, the president went on, Sierra Leone was given
the keys to freedom and chance to use these keys to open doors
that would keep national development, peace and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Today, however, there is evidence showing that Sierra Leone is
in a backward state, the president told the nation, adding that
it is because Sierra Leoneans do not like to see good things
about their fellow countrymen.
</P>
<P>
However, the president congratulated Sierra Leoneans for the
change he noted since the return of democracy and called on
everybody to move forward for a better tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Kabbah and his government was overthrown in a military coup in
May last year. He was only reinstated on March 10 this year
after the ousting of the illegal military regime.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
