<HEADLINE> Annan Appoints New MONUA Force Commander </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 27 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan Monday appointed Major-General Seth Kofi Obeng of Ghana
as the new force commander of the United Nations Observer Mission
in Angola (MONUA) to be effective at the end of April.
</P>
<P>
Born on January 26, 1945, Major-General Obeng joined the Ghana
Military Academy in 1963. He is also a graduate of the United
States Command and General Staff College, Fort Leavenworth.
</P>
<P>
Major-General Obeng served as a directing staff at the Ghana
Armed Forces Command and Staff College. He also served at the Army
Headquarters as General Officer Grade I, and deputy director of
military operations.
</P>
<P>
Major-General Obeng was appointed defense adviser at the
Ghanaian High Commission to the United Kingdom from 1984 to 1988.
From 1989 to 1991, and then from 1992 to 1993, he was seconded to
the State housing corporations as managing director.
</P>
<P>
From December 1993 to August 1994, he served as commandant of
the Military Academy and Training School, with additional
responsibility of commandant of the Ghana Armed Forces Staff
College. In October 1996, he became chief of staff at the General
Headquarters of the Ghana Armed Forces. 
</P>
