<HEADLINE> Posidonia'98 Shipping Fair to be Held in Piraeus, Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Posidonia'98, an international
shipping trade fair, will be held in the Greek port city of
Piraeus on June 1-5 this year.
</P>
<P>
The fair, the 16th in the series of international shipping
exhibitions, is sponsored by the Greek Merchant Marine Ministry,
the Municipality of Piraeus, the Hellenic Chamber of Shipping and
the Union of Greek Shipowners (UGS).
</P>
<P>
The trade fair will cover 19,500 square meters with the
participation of more than 1,350 exhibitors from 69 countries such
as Angola, Bangladesh, Chile, Ghana, Ireland, Latvia, Nigeria,
Slovenia, Tunisia, the United States and Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
A major increase will be seen in participation by exhibitors
specializing in software applications and computer consultancy
applied to ISM Code compliance and shipping office management
systems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
