<HEADLINE> French Customs Confiscates Fake World Cup Balls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Some 3,000 fake World Cup
"Tricolore" soccer balls have been confiscated from a ship from
India, French customs said in Marseille on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It was the second such case in four months following a haul of
1,000 counterfeit World Cup official balls from Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The genuine balls use the latest hi-tech materials and can
withstand the powerful kicks from the world class players.
</P>
</TEXT>
