<HEADLINE> Karachi Stock Exchange Index Goes Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Karachi Stock Exchange
(KSE)-100 Index lost 7.49 points on Tuesday to close at 1582.36
against Monday's close at 1589.85 points.
</P>
<P>
A total of 36 million shares were traded Tuesday against the 41
million shares on the previous day.
</P>
<P>
There were 63 gainers and 80 losers while share prices of 62
companies remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Analysts expect a further decline on the stock market as talks
are continuing between the government and independent power
producers on power tariff reduction.  
