<HEADLINE> Close Ties between FM Commissioner's Office, SAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Ma Yuzhen, commissioner of the
Chinese Foreign Ministry in the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (SAR), said here Tuesday that a close relationship of
cooperation has been established between his office and the SAR
government departments.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a luncheon hosted by the American Chamber of
Commerce in Hong Kong, Ma said: "We have also formed satisfactory
working relations with foreign consular offices."
</P>
<P>
Over the past nine months, he noted, "we have helped the SAR
government to send its officials to attend, as members of the
Chinese government delegation, over 40 international conferences
sponsored by some 20 inter-governmental organizations."
</P>
<P>
The Commissioner's Office has passed to the SAR government the
Central People's Government (CPG) instruments authorizing Hong
Kong to negotiate with 42 states 71 bilateral agreements in six
areas, including civil aviation.
</P>
<P>
The CPG has authorized the SAR government to formally sign 12
bilateral agreements with eight countries such as air services and
surrender of fugitive offenders.
</P>
<P>
It has also given a standing authorization to the SAR
government to negotiate visa exemption agreements or make
visa-free arrangements with foreign states, he said.
</P>
<P>
In close cooperation with the SAR government and Chinese
diplomatic missions overseas, he said the Commissioner's Office
has also handed 131 consular cases, including seven major
incidents involving the life or property of Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
"We have issued exequaturs to consuls-general and honorary
consuls representing 11 countries and consulted the views of the
SAR government on 25 consular post nominations submitted by
foreign states.
</P>
<P>
"We have handled and granted, upon the approval of the CPG,
diplomatic clearance for portcalls to 55 warships, of which 51 are
from the United States, and diplomatic clearance for landing or
flying over Hong Kong to 80 foreign military aircraft and VIP
planes, of which 61 are American," he said.
</P>
<P>
In order to do a good job in Hong Kong in accordance with the
principle of "one country, two systems," Ma said the
Commissioner's Office must be positioned in a proper way.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the relationship between Commissioner's Office
and the SAR government is not one of subordination but a
relationship of mutual respect, mutual trust, mutual support and
close cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"We shall render our full support and complete trust to the SAR
government in handling on its own the external affairs authorized
by the Basic Law so as to bring their initiatives into full play,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
It is imperative for the Commissioner's Office to combine
prudent attitude with pioneering spirit, proceed from the
realities of Hong Kong and seek solutions in a new environment
with a new approach, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ma said: "We and the SAR government have built an effective
working mechanism with clear division of responsibilities and
enjoyed satisfactory cooperation. We have also established good
working relations with foreign consular offices."
</P>
<P>
"Our smooth operation has been achieved mainly because of the
wisdom and practicability of 'one country, two systems', the
timely and explicit instructions from the CPG and the Foreign
Ministry, the valuable support of the SAR government and
cooperative efforts made by people of all walks of life in Hong
Kong, including foreign consular offices and foreign business
people," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
