<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing University Boasts Many Firsts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Beijing University, China's most
prestigious higher-learning institute, which will celebrate its
100th anniversary May 4, boasts many firsts in the country,
according to historical records.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1898, it was the first state-owned comprehensive
university in modern China. In 1903 its students launched the
country's first student movement, to protest against Russian
aggression.
</P>
<P>
Also in 1903, the school sent the first group of 46 Chinese
students to study abroad, and China's first national university
games were held on the university's campus.
</P>
<P>
In 1910 it became the first Chinese university to open
institutes on seven different subjects. And in 1917 the school set
up research bodies on mathematics, physics chemistry and the
Chinese classics, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Beijing University is known as the cradle of Marxism and
communism in China, as the country's first communist group
came into being here in 1920.
</P>
<P>
Coincidentally, in the same year, the university also became
the first in the country to admit girl students -- only three in
the beginning -- and allow them to sit together with boy students
in the same classrooms.
</P>
<P>
The university has China's largest school library, with more
than 4.5 million books, and the largest number of labs -- 116. It
also has the country's largest school museum.
</P>
<P>
It has engaged in exchanges with 143 universities in 40
foreign countries and regions, ranking first among all Chinese
universities.
</P>
<P>
Beijing University now has eight institutes, 21 departments, 52
research institutes and 63 research centers, ranking first in the
country in terms of the number of subjects taught.
</P>
<P>
The Founder Group of Beijing University is the country's
largest school-run enterprise. It generated a total income of
nearly six billion yuan (723 million US dollars) in
1997. Moreover, the Founder Group is China's first school-owned
firm listed on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
Finally, Beijing University is well known for its 80-plus
student groups which are the basis for the school's colorful
campus life. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980428.0075 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines' Inflation Rate Seen to Rise This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' inflation rate is
expected to rise this year due to the effect of the El Nino
weather phenomenon and the impact of the regional currency crisis,
the Central Bank of the Philippines said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"While expected to remain single-digit, inflation is
nevertheless projected to rise in 1998," the central bank said in
an annual report issued here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The bank blamed El Nino and high costs of imported goods and
interest rates caused by the financial crisis for the expected
rise in the inflation rate.
</P>
<P>
The El Nino phenomenon, which hit the country late last year,
has caused a massive drought in the southern island of Mindanao,
dealing a severe blow to agricultural production.
</P>
<P>
But the bank did not say whether the average inflation rate for
1998 could reach its earlier estimated level of between 7.5 and
8.5 percent. Last year, the country's inflation rate averaged 5.1
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
