<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Launches Patent Application Grant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- To stay competitive in the Asia
region, Hong Kong will need to add value to its commercial and
industrial activities through innovation and technology
development, a Hong Kong official said here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Hosting a launching ceremony of the Patent Application Grant,
Director-General of Industry Francis Ho said that there is a need
for fostering innovation in the local industry.
</P>
<P>
This is in line with the one of the missions of the newly
established Chief Executive's Commission on Innovation and
Technology, which is to make Hong Kong an innovation center for
the region, the official noted.
</P>
<P>
The grant will assist local companies and individuals to apply
for patent registration of their own inventions.
</P>
<P>
The Industry Department has made available an initial sum of 6
million HK dollars (769,000 U.S. dollars) to start off the pilot
scheme for a period of three years.
</P>
<P>
The scheme will be open for all locally incorporated companies
or Hong Kong permanent residents who have never owned any patents
before.
</P>
<P>
All functional patents and inventions (except cosmetic designs)
are eligible.
</P>
<P>
The applications will go through a patent search and a
technical appraisal by the implementation agencies to ensure that
there is little chance of infringement on existing patents and
demonstrate a reasonable chance of success.
</P>
<P>
The grant will be used to cover the direct costs involved in
the patent application process, such as pre-application technical
appraisal, attorney fees, consultant fees and filing of
applications.
</P>
<P>
Application forms for the scheme can be obtained from the
Industry Department and the two implementation agencies -- the
Hong Kong Productivity Council and the Hong Kong Institute of
Biotechnology Ltd. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
