<HEADLINE> American Boat Penalised in 7th Leg of Whitbread Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 28 (Xinhua) -- American yacht Toshiba has been
penalised two places in the seventh leg of the Whitbread Round the
World race for crossing too close in front of a rival boat.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here from Southampton, England,
Toshiba has dropped to last place from seventh in the leg which
finished in Baltimore, the United States, last week.
</P>
<P>
Her overall position remains unchanged at seventh on 363 points.
</P>
<P>
The international race jury found that Toshiba had crossed too
close in front of Swedish boat EF Education on the first night of
the leg, forcing the crew to take evasive action to avoid a
collision.
</P>
<P>
Toshiba crew said they completed a 720-degree turn immediately
as a penalty but did not record this in their log book to verify.
</P>
</TEXT>
