<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK's Development Proves One country, Two Systems Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese official said here
Tuesday that the developments in Hong Kong over the past nine
months since the handover last July proves the absolute
correctness of the "one country, two systems" policy.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a luncheon hosted by the American Chamber of
Commerce in Hong Kong, Ma Yuzhen, commissioner of the Chinese
Foreign Ministry in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR), said that the situation in the HKSAR is, on the whole,
very good.
</P>
<P>
The principles of "one country, two systems", "Hong Kong people
administering Hong Kong", and a high degree of autonomy and the
Basic Law have been fully implemented, he said.
</P>
<P>
The previous social system and lifestyle in Hong Kong have
remained unchanged, and the laws in Hong Kong basically unchanged.
Hong Kong has been operating smoothly in all aspects, he added.
</P>
<P>
"All these have ensured Hong Kong's continued prosperity and
stability," he said, adding that the SAR Government headed by
Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa has excelled itself with a
highly-effective administrative performance.
</P>
<P>
He pointed to a remarkable achievement that Hong Kong has made
especially in the wake of the Asian financial crisis that has
produced some adverse effects on Hong Kong. He described the
counter-measures adopted by the SAR Government as firm,
appropriate, and effective.
</P>
<P>
As a result, he said the financial and economic situation in
the SAR has, on the whole, remained stable.
</P>
<P>
Over the past nine months, the commissioner said that the
Central People's Government (CPG) has steadfastly implemented in
Hong Kong the principles of "one country, two systems", "Hong Kong
people administering Hong Kong", and a high degree of autonomy and
the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
This is because these basic guidelines not only serve the
immediate and long-term interests of Hong Kong, but also fully
conform to China's overall national interests.
</P>
<P>
They constitute the fundamental guarantee for Hong Kong's
long-term prosperity and stability and they are state policies
aimed at early reunification of the whole of China and
revitalization of the Chinese nation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ma said that facts have proved that the determination of the
CPG to implement the concept of "one country, two systems" is by
no means lip-service but a serious commitment substantiated with
actual deeds. It is definitely not an expedient or something
temporary, but a firm commitment to be honored for decades to
come.
</P>
<P>
He said the CPG has complete trust in the SAR Government and
given it full support and a free hand in administering Hong Kong
in accordance with the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
The CPG has fully supported the SAR Government in its recent
efforts to stabilize Hong Kong's financial market. A good
relationship has been established between the CPG and the SAR
Government.
</P>
<P>
Ma said the great concept of "one country, two systems" has now
become a reality in Hong Kong, which proves that Hong Kong
residents composed mainly of Chinese have both the determination
and ability to run Hong Kong well.
</P>
<P>
It proves that the SAR government headed by Tung Chee Hwa has
both the wisdom and experience to steer Hong Kong through
complicated situation smoothly and to maintain its prosperity and
stability.
</P>
<P>
It also proves that the motherland is the solid and strong
support base for the HKSAR in its endeavor to maintain prosperity
and stability and to tide over difficulties and risks in its
course of development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
