<HEADLINE> Express Train Derails in East India, Killing 10 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 28 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 people were killed
and more than 30 injured Tuesday morning when an express train
derailed in Bihari state in east India, the Press Trust of India
(PTI) reported.
</P>
<P>
The train derailed at 0730 hours near the Bankaghat railway
station, about 18 kilometers from Patna, capital of the state.
</P>
<P>
The PTI quoted a district official as saying that 15 of the
injured were in serious condition.
</P>
<P>
Indian Railway Minister Nitish Kumar, who is now on a tour of
Patna, rushed to the accident site and expressed profound grief
over the tragedy.
</P>
<P>
Railway sources did not rule out sabotage in the accident.
</P>
<P>
Reports from the accident site said a fish plate was found to
be removed while another was missing over the rail bridge where
the accident occurred.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday, 24 passengers were killed and 36 others injured
when a goods train rammed into a stationary express in the
southwestern state of Maharashtra.
</P>
<P>
In another accident on Tuesday, six school children were killed
and 17 others injured when two rickshaws carrying them were hit by
a speeding bus near Farrukhabad in the northeast Uttar Pradesh.
</P>
</TEXT>
