<HEADLINE> Beijing Has Over 1.74 Million Skilled People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has more than 1.74
million skilled people, 65 percent of whom are professionals
working in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Also among them are 12,000 postgraduates and 169,000 graduates,
accounting for 1.4 percent and 19.5 percent of the total. Those
with two- or three-year college education, or secondary vocational
or high school education constitute 29.3 percent, 29.9 percent and
19.9 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Compared with other provinces and municipalities, Beijing
boasts the largest and best-qualified proportion of skilled
people, said Xin Tieliang, deputy director of the Beijing
Municipal Personnel Bureau, with pride at a news conference on the
city's personnel resources today.
</P>
<P>
On the conception of skilled people, Xin said it refers to
those who have finished a course at a secondary vocational school,
have obtained a professional title or who function in leading
posts.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Beijing has a strong capacity for fostering
talent, as some 50,000-60,000 students graduate from the city's 65
higher education institutes each year.
</P>
<P>
Other education units, including adult colleges and various
training schools, also graduate nearly 200,000 people each
year, he added.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the structure of skilled professionals in the Chinese
capital is becoming more rational, Xin said, and an increasing
number of young professionals have been taking up various posts in
recent years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
