<HEADLINE> Japan Edges China 104-100 in Women's Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Japan edged China 104-100 in a game
at the four-nation women's basketball tournament in Nagoya, Japan
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 1994 World Championship runner-up China squandered a 51-45
half-time lead and was forced to a 100-100 tie with just 25
seconds left before Takako Kato put Japan ahead with two free
throws.
</P>
<P>
In the other match, Michelle Griffiths scored 21 points as
Australia handed the United States their first loss at the
tournament.
</P>
<P>
Australia, the 1996 Olympic bronze medalist, led 35-29 at
halftime before winning 70-53.
</P>
<P>
Katie Smith led the United States with 12 points, followed by
Lisa Leslie scored 9, while Ruthie Bolton and Tina Thompson 7 each.
</P>
<P>
Australia and the United States now tied for the lead at the
double round-robin tournament with three wins and one loss. Japan
was 2-2 while China 0-4.
</P>
<P>
Japan meets Australia and the United States faces China in
Tokyo on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The four teams are preparing for the World Championships in
Germany from May 26-June 7. 
