<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Rise by 0.8 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks rose 84.90
points, or 0.80 percent, to close at 10,678.61 on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The market's turnover amounted to 6,574 million HK dollars
(842.82 Million U.S. dollars), 355 million HK dollars (45.5
million U.S. dollars) more than that of Monday.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index fell 279.09 points, or 2.6 percent, to
10,314.62 as it was opened on Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
It further declined 141.23 points, or 1.33 percent, to finish
at 10,452.48 at midday.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong share prices fell 286.22 points, or 2.63 percent, to
close at 10,593.71 on Monday.  
</P>
