<HEADLINE> New Book Reprints Articles on Ideology from 'New Youth' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- A publisher in central China's
Henan Province has published a book with more than 500 selected
articles from an influential periodical encompassing modern
China's ideology early this century.
</P>
<P>
The articles, all published in the original style, were chosen
from the New Youth, a periodical existing from 1915 to 1922 mainly
discussing radicals and conservatives, obsolete and new morals,
democracy, science, freedom and liberation.
</P>
<P>
Much of the discussion has continued to today, and that's why
the articles are published again, according to a spokesman for the
Henan Literature and Art Press.
</P>
<P>
Hu Shi, a well-known modern Chinese ideologist, used to regard
New Youth as a periodical dividing an era, and opening the heart
of the Chinese to the world.
</P>
<P>
At a recent book fair in Beijing the book, titled "Reading New
Youth Again," caught the attention of many media and book
stores. Managers of some big stores here said that they are
optimistic about sales.
</P>
<P>
The book's publisher donated 12 books to Beijing University
today to honor the school's May 4 centennial. The university was a
major supporter of New Youth early this century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
