of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) with more reports
carried in major Chinese newspapers in recent days.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony of the NPC session on April 26,
reporters from all the state-level press organizations covered the
event.
</P>
<P>
China's leading newspaper, "People's Daily," sent a five-member
crew to the meeting and devoted whole pages in the paper both
Monday and today. The newspaper plans to publish a special page on
the NPC system each month.
</P>
