<HEADLINE> China to Get Tougher on Crime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- China's national police force of
1 million has been mobilized to crack down on criminal activities,
especially those endangering the social order, according to an
urgent circular released today by the Ministry of Public Security.
</P>
<P>
"In general, China enjoys a stable social order," the circular
reads, "but in certain areas of the country, social order is not so
optimistic."
</P>
<P>
The circular urges public security bureaus at all levels to
concentrate on cracking down on major criminal cases, criminal
rings and escaped criminals in an effort to guarantee a stable
social environment across the country.
</P>
<P>
The national police force has also been ordered to tighten the
management of firearms and explosives and to improve order in
public places.
</P>
<P>
The circular requires public security bureaus nationwide to
strengthen the cooperation among police departments to improve the
combat effectiveness of the national police force.  
</P>
</TEXT>
