<HEADLINE> Beijing Needs More Skilled Professionals, Official Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital is badly in
need of competent managerial personnel, academicians, high-tech
talent and those with two or more kinds of professional skills, a
municipal official said here today.
</P>
<P>
High-tech industries, service trades and private enterprises
will attract more competent people in the future, said Xin
Tieliang, deputy director of the Beijing Municipal Personnel
Bureau, at a news conference on the city's personnel resources.
</P>
<P>
Government departments will want fewer people now that
institutional restructuring is under way, Xin said.
</P>
<P>
The total human resources and demand for skilled professionals
will be approximately even in Beijing this year, the official
said.
</P>
<P>
Some 75,000 will graduate from institutions of higher learning,
secondary professional schools and adult schools, or retire from
the army this year. On the other hand, the total demand for such
people is about 70,000.
</P>
<P>
However, Xin said structural problems remain, explaining that
those studying specialties such as computer science, machinery,
industrial automation, marketing, architecture and foreign
languages will be more in demand.  
</P>
</TEXT>
