<HEADLINE> 68 Kilograms of Drugs Seized in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- A total of 68 kilograms of drugs
has been seized in eastern Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia
News Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The drugs, including 29 kilograms of heroin and 39 kilograms of
hashish, were confiscated by the Turkish police during a search
in Yuksekova town of Van province linking neighboring Iran, the
agency said.
</P>
<P>
The drugs were found buried under the land near a house at
Esentepe district in the town, it said, without giving further
details.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and Iran are on the transit route of drug trafficking to
Europe from the border areas of Afghanistan and Pakistan. In 1996,
Turkish police seized 4.4 tons of heroin, which accounted for 40
percent of the world's total haul. 
</P>
</TEXT>
