<HEADLINE> Shanghai Promotes Use of Liquid Petroleum Gas in Taxis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai will have its 20,000
taxis renovated to use liquid petroleum gas (LPG) within five
years as a measure to reduce pollution.
</P>
<P>
This was announced today by a leading government official in a
ceremony marking the building of an LPG filling station.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, Shanghai had built two such filling
stations and more than 100 taxis were restructured to use either
petrol or LPG.
</P>
<P>
The official said that Shanghai will build four more LPG
filling stations and have 2,000 taxis renovated to use LPG this
year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Shanghai will also remodel its buses so that they
can use both petrol and LPG, he said.  
</P>
