<HEADLINE> Iran Seizes 6 Tonnes of Narcotics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Iran seized six tonnes of
narcotics in the northeastern province of Khorasan during the
first month of this Iranian year (started March 21), the Iranian
newspaper Jomhuri Islami reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The provincial commander of the security forces Bahram Nurouzi
was quoted as saying on Monday that the drugs were seized in 75
anti-drug operations.
</P>
<P>
In addition, other 2.5 tonnes of narcotics were seized during
the past 24 hours, he added.
</P>
<P>
The confiscated drugs were valued at 2.5 billion rials (about
830,000 U.S. dollars), Nurouzi said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said that 187 tonnes of narcotics were seized
in the country during the last Iranian year, including 83 percent
of opium, 11 percent morphine, five percent hashish and one
percent heroin. 
