<HEADLINE> Albright on New U.S.-Japan Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 28 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright said here Tuesday a new logistical support agreement
between the United States and Japan is not directed at any
particular country or region, including the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
"This is not directed at any particular region or country and
is a functional agreement for logistical assistance," Albright
said in a joint news conference with Japanese Foreign Minister
Keizo Obuchi.
</P>
<P>
