agreement to revise the Japan-U.S. Acquisition and Cross-Servicing
Agreement (ACSA) to expand bilateral cooperation for the supply of
fuel, food and transportation in emergencies in so-called "areas
surrounding Japan."
</P>
<P>
Shortly before the Albright-Obuchi talks, the Japanese
government adopted two bills to implement updated
Japan-U.S. defense cooperation guidelines as well as a draft
revision of the ACSA.
</P>
<P>
Tokyo and Washington agreed last September on the revised
version of the 1978 bilateral defense cooperation guidelines.
</P>
<P>
Albright arrived here earlier in the day for a two-day visit to
Japan. 
</P>
