<HEADLINE> China, Kyrghyz Sign Joint Statement (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The two sides spoke highly of the five-nation accord on
increasing military trust and reducing their military presence in
the border areas. The accord was signed by China, Russia,
Kazakhstan, Kyrghyzstan and Tajikistan. Both China and the Kyrghyz
Republic have determined to take effective steps to implement the
accord to further promote peace, security, stability and
prosperity in the border areas.
</P>
<P>
They also agree that great potential exists for further
expanding and deepening bilateral economic and trade cooperation,
which they describe as an important part of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
The two countries will take advantage of their geographic
proximity and encourage bilateral firms to have direct contact and
increase investment in each other.
</P>
<P>
They will prioritize fields of energy resources, mining,
nonferrous metals, light industry, textiles, electrical home
appliances and agriculture for mutually beneficial cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Both nations will also study the possibility of Kyrghyzstan's
supply of electricity to China or to a third country via China.
</P>
<P>
Great prospects for bilateral cooperation exist in textiles and
light industry as well as the processing industry, they said, and
relevant enterprises will be encouraged to invest in each other.
</P>
<P>
Both hold that the forms of cooperation can be varied,
including the leasing of equipment, joint research and renewal of
equipment, transfer of technology and shared entry into a
third-country market.
</P>
<P>
They will also further develop and improve the road, rail and
aviation links between the two nations, adding that they think it
is of great importance to build a railway among China, Kyrghyzstan
and Uzbekistan.
</P>
<P>
They agreed to make joint efforts to further expand border
transportation between the two countries, and to promote bilateral
scientific and technological cooperation.
</P>
<P>
They also plan to tighten cooperation on environmental
protection issues.
</P>
