<HEADLINE> China Tourism Festival Initiated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The China Tourism Festival opened
here today at a newly built scenic spot to the east of the Chinese
capital.
</P>
<P>
The large tourism promotion activity is being jointly sponsored
by the China National Tourism Administration (CNTA) and the China
International Trust and Investment Corp. (CITIC).
</P>
<P>
The festival will last 40 days at the "Top City Under Heaven"
in the Tongzhou District of Beijing. With a coverage of 1.33
million square meters, the "City" is based on the layout of
ancient Beijing's city walls and gate towers. It includes
sight-seeing spots, amusement parks, shopping areas, catering
services and accommodations and it features royal culture and
folklore. The city is considered a replica of ancient Beijing and
a miniature of Chinese history.
</P>
<P>
The city was built at a cost of more than 700 million
yuan. Work began in 1992,
</P>
<P>
The China Tourism Festival -- with the subject of "peace,
progress, and happiness" -- is a part of the CNTA-sponsored '98
China City and Country Tours.
</P>
<P>
After the successful launch of '97 China Tourism Year, the
country put forward its famous historical and cultural cities and
countryside folklore tourism this year with a goal of improving on
last year's 640 million domestic tourists and 57.6 million
overseas tourists.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Qian Qichen attended today's opening ceremony.
</P>
</TEXT>
