<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets South Korean Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Vice-President Hu
Jintao said Tuesday that China is satisfied with the fast growth
of bilateral cooperation since the two forged diplomatic ties in
1992.
</P>
<P>
In his meeting with South Korean Foreign and Trade Minister
Park Chung-soo here, Hu said that the Chinese government attaches
importance to its ties with South Korea and is ready to work with
the South Korean side to maintain the momentum of the contact
between the leaders of the two countries, strictly abide by the
principles confirmed when the two countries established diplomatic
ties and expand bilateral economic and trade cooperation on the
basis of mutual-benefit to promote the joint development and
prosperity of the two countries and the region.
</P>
<P>
China is also ready to expand the exchange between the youths
of the two countries, Hu said, adding that Sino-South Korean
good-neighborly and friendly ties oriented toward the next century
would be further consolidated and advanced with efforts of both
sides.
</P>
<P>
Describing Hu's present South Korea trip as a successful one,
Park said that the visit would greatly promote South Korea-China
relations.
</P>
<P>
He told Hu that the South Korean government would strictly
adhere to its commitment on the issue of Taiwan and would not have
official relations with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Park said that bilateral ties have maintained a good momentum
of development since the two countries established diplomatic
relations,with which South Korean side is satisfied.
</P>
<P>
South Korea is willing to strengthen its relations in various
fields with China, Park said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
