<HEADLINE> China's Development Important to Regional Stability: Kim </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 28 (Xinhua)-- South Korean President Kim Dae-jung
said Tuesday that China's development is of great importance
to peace and stability on the Korean peninsula as well as in
the Asian-Pacific region in the next century.
</P>
<P>
Kim, who made the remarks while meeting with visiting Chinese
Vice-President Hu Jintao here, said that Hu's tour will further
enhance relations between South Korea and China.
</P>
<P>
China's development is also a great help to South Korea, said
Kim, adding that he is looking forward to visiting China at an
early date.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Hu expressed his appreciation of Kim's
dedication to the growth of relations between China and South
Korea. The remarkable development in bilateral ties achieved over
the past five years is not only in line with the fundamental
interests of the two peoples, but also conducive to peace,
stability and development on the Korean peninsula, Hu added.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the Korean peninsula problems, Hu said that the
Chinese government has always been striving for the maintenance of
peace and stability in the area, which is China's basic principle
concerning the affairs on the peninsula.
</P>
<P>
China hopes that both sides on the peninsula would promote
mutual understanding and trust, and improve their relations
gradually through contacts and dialogue to create environment for
the realization of self-reliance and peaceful reunification,
the Chinese vice-president added.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the two sides also exchanged views on
bilateral ties and other issues of common concern. 
</P>
</TEXT>
