<HEADLINE> S. Africa Joins World Paper Giant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Global paper producer Sappi has
integrated its four international fine paper operations to create
Sappi Fine Paper, the world's first and largest global coated fine
paper company, local daily the Citizen reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The new Sappi Fine Paper will have sales of approximately 20
billion Rand (four billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
This will contribute nearly 80 percent of Sappi's turnover and
giving Sappi a dominant 26 percent share of the American market, 22
percent of the European market and 60 percent of the African market in
coated woodfree papers used in quality publications such as high
quality magazines, annual reports, brochures, art books and calendars.
</P>
<P>
Sappi Fine Papers will be managed from Brussels for the European
operations, Johannesburg for the African operations and Boston for
North America.
</P>
<P>
Sales in Asia and South America will be handled through Sappi
Trading, which continues to operate out of HongKong.
</P>
<P>
Johannesburg is the commercial hub of South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Sappi Forest Products will be headquartered in Johannesburg and is
South Africa's leading producer of pulp and kraft packaging paper.
</P>
</TEXT>
