<HEADLINE> 50,000 Alumni of Beijing University To Join Centennial Celebration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- More than 50,000 alumni of the
prestigious Beijing University will come back to take part in the
celebration activities of the centennial anniversary on May 4,
according to an official of the university.
</P>
<P>
Along with the alumni, 140 presidents of world-renowned
universities and more than 2,000 Chinese and foreign experts in
various fields as well as responsible members of some 80 world
famous enterprises will attend the celebration, said Ren Yanshen,
Party Secretary of Beijing University.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, 190,000 alumni around the world will
celebrate the foundation of their alma mater in different ways.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 activities including 14 international academic
conventions started this week, according to Ren, who is
responsible for the celebration.
</P>
<P>
Ren said 97 Chinese news media and more than 50 overseas media
have signed up in the report about Beijing University.
</P>
<P>
At today's news conference, foreign journalists asked whether
U.S. President Bill Clinton would visit Beijing University during
his visit to China in June. Chi Huisheng, vice-president of
Beijing University, said the U.S. Embassy in China has contacted
the university three times.
</P>
<P>
"And a delegation from the U.S. has come to inspect the
university. But the visit has yet to be set by foreign affairs
departments of the two countries," Chi answered.
</P>
<P>
According to Chi, delegations from six Taiwan universities will
attend the forum of presidents of world-renowned universities,
which will be held during the celebration. At present, 48 students
from Taiwan are studying at the university.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released at today's news conference show that among
the 1,000 academicians of the Chinese Academy of Sciences and the
Chinese Academy of Engineering, 396 either received their
education or worked at Beijing University.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the university has 23 departments and eight
institutes enrolling 24,000 students, including 5,500 graduate
students and more than 2,000 foreign students. More than 3,000
teachers and scientific researchers are employed by the university.
</P>
<P>
The university has signed exchange agreements with 143
universities in more than 40 countries and regions, and an average
of 300 foreign experts are invited to lecture at the university
annually.  
</P>
</TEXT>
