<DOCNO> XIE19980428.0158 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Banking Simulation Center Receives DEC Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Experimental Banking
Simulation Center operated by the People's Bank of China (PBOC),
the nation's central bank, signed a memorandum of cooperation
today with U.S.-based Digital Equipment Company.
</P>
<P>
The center, the first of its kind in China, will enter
operations in April following receipt of DEC's donation of an
Alpha Server computer and accompanying software.
</P>
<P>
DEC General Manager Thomas Lam presented a speech at the
signing ceremony and noted that the event marks the beginning of
cooperation between his company and the PBOC.
</P>
<P>
He said that the drive to modernize China's financial sector
will require talented professionals with extensive expertise in
both finance and information technology.
</P>
<P>
The center is a major participant in the national priority
research project listed in "China's Modern Payment System."
</P>
<P>
The experimental center will use state-of-the-art computer
technology to simulate and solve problems in banking operations
and the overall financial system.
</P>
<P>
It will also serve as a research base for applications of
information technology for the central bank's decision-making
process and supervision of the financial sector.
</P>
<P>
The center is located at the Southwestern University of Finance
and Economies in Chengdu, Sichuan Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
