<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Meets Kyrghyz President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- China's policy of developing
trans-century friendship and relations of cooperation with the
Kyrghyz Republic will remain unchanged, Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji
pledged in a meeting this morning with visiting Kyrghyz President
Askar Akyevich Akayev.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that China values very much its friendship with Kyrghyz,
adding that the Chinese government will continue to actively
promote cooperation in various sectors between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that Monday, Akayev's talks with Chinese President
Jiang Zemin were fruitful and wished his current visit to China a
great success.
</P>
<P>
Akayev congratulated Zhu for his serving as Chinese premier and
spoke highly of the progress made in bilateral friendly relations
in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Akayev said Kyrghyz-China cooperation has become the locomotive
for the economic development of his country. Akayev said he hoped
bilateral relations oriented toward the 21st century would be
further developed and raised to a new high.
</P>
<P>
Zhu stressed that China and the Kyrghyz Republic, as good
neighbors, have many convenient conditions in their economic and
trade cooperation. Although the current trade volume between the
two countries is not large, potential of bilateral cooperation
remains to be tapped, he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said the pivotal points are to take the market demand into
account, choose the right projects for cooperation and proceed
step by step. Zhu said he believed economic and trade cooperation
between the two countries would reach a new level as long as both
sides take concrete measures.  
</P>
</TEXT>
