<HEADLINE> Powerful Explosion at Kalutara In Southern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 28 (Xinhua) -- A powerful bomb exploded Monday
night at the Kalutara Telecommunications office in the Eastern
Province of Sri Lanka, media reports reaching here said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The bomb blast totally destroyed the radio equipment which
services thousands of telephone connections in the area from the
Kalutara telephone exchange, 45 kilometers from Colombo.
</P>
<P>
No one was killed or injured in the explosion, the reports
said.
</P>
<P>
The exchange is partly owned and managed by the Japanese Nippon
Telegraph and Telephone (NTT) company under Sri Lanka's
privatization scheme.
</P>
<P>
Police are conducting investigations into the incident and have
not ruled out the possibility of Tamil rebels being involved, the
reports said.
</P>
<P>
The explosion came amid tight security in the Sri Lanka capital
following a series of bomb attacks in recent months. The Tamil
rebels have been fighting a 15-year-old war for a separate state
in the north and east of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
