<HEADLINE> Cloud-seeding Produces Artificial Rainfall in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's crops have benefited
from artificial rainfall three times since the beginning of April
because of the efforts of the Beijing Meteorological Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Today's Beijing Youth Daily said that, with help from the air
force, the bureau used balloons to launch 120 silver iodide bombs
in five suburban counties on the morning of April 23 followed by a
moderate rain.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the artificial rainfall, which was the city's most
successful springtime cloud-seeding, Beijing also has launched
operations for producing artificial snow, preventing hail and
expelling fog.
</P>
<P>
The fog-expelling operations were launched last winter to
guarantee safe air traffic.  
</P>
