<HEADLINE> Officials Punished for Squandering Public Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- An official in north China's
Hebei Province was recently dismissed from his post for his
misappropriation of public funds to purchase mobile phones for
personal use.
</P>
<P>
Hu Taian, former director of the Luancheng County Power Supply
Bureau, misappropriated 867,000 yuan of public funds to purchase
70 mobile phones and pay telephone bills for use by the bureau's
140 staffers. He was also convicted of attempting to bribe his
supervisor with illegally purchased mobile phones.
</P>
<P>
Hu's prosecution triggered an new wave of investigations of
similar cases in Luancheng and the city of Shijiazhuang, capital
of Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
The Shijiazhuang Department for Discipline Inspection launched
an investigative blitz which uncovered a total of 2,991 mobile
phones illegally purchased with public funds.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,076 mobile phones auctioned at discount prices resulted
in the recovery of public funds totalling 5.19 million yuan.
</P>
