<HEADLINE> Planning Commission Calls for Improved Power Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The State Development Planning
Commission has released a notice urging local pricing departments
to improve management over electricity prices in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
Today's People's Daily reported that related efforts will
greatly ease unreasonable burdens on farmers.
</P>
<P>
The notice defines electricity prices in rural areas in two
categories -- prices charged by county-level power supply firms
serving township electricity management stations, and maintenance
fees for low-pressure power grids in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
"All fees beyond the two clearly defined categories are illegal
and must be banned," according to the notice.
</P>
<P>
The notice lists ceiling prices for maintenance fees as 0.25
yuan/kwh in east China and Guangdong Province, 0.20 yuan in
northeast, north and central regions, and 0.15 yuan in the
southwest and northwest.
</P>
<P>
The notice called on local governments to unify price and
provide detailed information to farmers.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey conducted by the commission shows that
electricity prices charged by some local governments are subject
to additional fee items. Additional fees charged nationwide stand
at 21.7 billion yuan annually. 
</P>
</TEXT>
