<HEADLINE> Former State Institutions Adopt Differing Strategies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Restructured state institutions
have adopted different approaches for dealing with obsolete items
such as nameplates, official seals. letterheads and envelopes.
</P>
<P>
For example, nameplates for the former State Physical Culture
and Sports Commission and Ministry of Radio, Film and Television,
as well as the Ministry of Geology and Mineral Resources have been
placed in museums.
</P>
<P>
However, the nameplate of the former Ministry of Internal Trade
was relegated to the carpentry shop. "The ministry has changed its
name several times and has always discarded obsolete nameplates,"
according to an official from the former ministry.
</P>
<P>
Various institutions continue to use outdated letterheads and
envelopes internally.
</P>
<P>
New institutions have introduced new official seals, with
outdated seals returned to the General Office of the State
Council.  
