<HEADLINE> Telephone Service to Be Improved in E. Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- A modern digital telephone
exchange system is to be installed in Uganda's eastern Jinja area
to attract investment and boost local economy, The New Vision
paper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Richard Owora, Principal Public Relations Officer of the
Uganda Telecommunications Limited (UTL), said the new exchange
system is imported from Japan and the installation in Jinja will
begin soon as the staff responsible for installation work had
returned from training in Japan.
</P>
<P>
He said that the system, with a capacity of 10,000 lines,
will be commissioned before the end of the year and only 3,000
lines will be given to first subscribers due to lack of resources
to operate to full capacity.
</P>
<P>
There has long been an outcry from the region for more and
better telephone service. The present system, installed in 1971,
is too much out of date, local people complained. 
</P>
</TEXT>
