<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hail Kills Three in Sichuan Province; Damages Homes, Farms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Strong hail storms in southwest
China's Sichuan Province killed three people and seriously injured
45 last week.
</P>
<P>
From April 22 to 24, 31 county-level administrative areas in
Sichuan were pelted by hail, with a top wind velocity of 21 meters
per second and the biggest hail measuring 18 centimeters in
diameter.
</P>
<P>
According to sources with the provincial disaster-relief
office, more than 9,400 houses were destroyed and another 32,700
houses were damaged. In addition, 87,300 hectares of farmland were
damaged by hail.
</P>
<P>
The hail also caused 190 million yuan (22.9 million
U.S. dollars) in losses to telecommunications, electric power and
transportation facilities.
</P>
<P>
In the cities of Neijiang and Deyang, the hail lasted 30
minutes, and hail as heavy as one kilogram covered the ground to
depths of 30 centimeters.
</P>
<P>
According to provincial sources, 100,000 households in Sichuan
are leading a hard life with local residents badly in need of
water and grain.
</P>
<P>
Following the disasters, local governments have immediately
organized rescue teams, dispatched relief supplies and assisted
local farmers with their crops. 
</P>
</TEXT>
