<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand's Exports to Japanese Market Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BANGKOK, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's exports for the first
quarter of this year dropped by 2.8 percent in dollar terms
compared to the same period last year, primarily due to a 10
percent decline in the Japanese market, according to the Thai
Commerce Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Exports to Japanese market between January-March stood at 13
billion U.S. dollars, a fall from 13.2 billion U.S. dollars,
compared to the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The poor performance in the Japanese market brought Thailand's
monthly exports in at lower than the projected 5 billion baht
(12.5 million U.S. dollars) a month.
</P>
<P>
The decline in the Japanese market has caused such concern
among the Thai government that Deputy Prime Minister and Commerce
Minister Supachai Panitchpakdi will hold discussions with Japan's
Ministry of International Trade and Investment to find a solution
to the problem, a source at the Thai Commerce ministry was quoted
Tuesday by the Bangkok Post as saying.
</P>
<P>
Japan was the Thailand's second largest market, but fell to
south place last year, after ASEAN, the United states and EU.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
