<HEADLINE> Sofia, Moscow Agree on Cooperation in Natural Gas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria and Russia agreed here
Monday to increase Russia's natural gas supply to Bulgaria and other
countries via Bulgaria, according to Bulgarian Telegraph Agency.
</P>
<P>
Russia's natural gas company Gazprom chief Rem Vyakhirev and
Bulgarian Deputy Prime Minister Evgenii Bakurdjiev signed a
memorandum on the matter.
</P>
<P>
Under the memorandum, Bulgaria is obliged to expand the
facilities for transmitting gas from Russia to Turkey, Greece,
Serbia and Macedonia. On its part, Russia agreed that 20 percent
of the cost of the gas supplied could be paid in labor and goods.
</P>
<P>
This is mutually beneficial, said Vyakhirev and Bakurdjiev
after the signing ceremony. 
</P>
