<HEADLINE> Sichuan Province Suffers Severe Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan
Province has witnessed severe drought since last summer, according
to today's People's Daily.
</P>
<P>
Local government statistics released on April 23 show that
116 out of the province's 180 counties have suffered from
drought conditions.
</P>
<P>
The prolonged drought has adversely affected some 1.4 million
ha. of summer grain crops, with significantly heavy damage to
grain crops planted on 53,000 hectares.
</P>
<P>
The lack of water prevented farmers from planting rice
seedlings on 530,000 ha., and 10 percent of cotton and corn
seedlings have withered.
</P>
<P>
The local government has listed the battle against the drought
as a top priority and has allocated eight million yuan for
minimizing losses.  
</P>
</TEXT>
