<HEADLINE> Beijing to Cooperate with Transnational Corporations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Beijing, the Chinese capital,
will open wider to the outside world by developing new and high
technology on the basis of cooperation with transnational
corporations, according to today's Beijing Daily.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a Monday forum attended by management personnel
from the capital's large transnational corporations, Beijing Mayor
Jia Qinglin said the city has a sound base which will enable
transnational corporations to develop new and high technology
ventures.
</P>
<P>
Jia noted that 148 of the world's 500 major transnational
corporations have opened branches in Beijing, in addition to
investing in some 400-odd projects.
</P>
<P>
Beijing's new and high technology ventures have
witnessed an average annual growth rate of 30 percent over the
past decade.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investment in related ventures is expected to focus on
the information industry, electronic information processing,
bioengineering, pharmaceuticals and new materials.
</P>
<P>
First quarter foreign investment in the city grew by 15 percent
on the previous year's quarter to 940 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing New Technology Development and Experimental Zone,
Beijing Economic and Technological Development Zone, Beijing
Electronics Zone and Beijing Airport Industrial Zone will continue
to serve as bases for new and high technology ventures.  
</P>
</TEXT>
