<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Troops Launch Operation "Tiger Hunt" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Army and Navy have
launched a joint operation code named "Tiger Hunt" to flush out
Tamil rebels from the North of Trincomalee in the Eastern
province, the Sinhalese Diwarna newspaper report Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Military sources were quoted as saying that the military thrust
which commenced from Fowl Point, saw the Tamil rebels ousted from
their camps at Sampur and Iththikulam.
</P>
<P>
While the Army has also surrounded rebel camps at Weragala and
Mahindapura, the Navy is keeping vigil in the nearby sea front to
prevent rebel cadres from escaping by sea.
</P>
<P>
The rebels in the course of their escape attempts had blasted
the ferry at Weragala to prevent the government troops from using
it.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam have
been waging a 15-year war against the government for a separate
state in the North and East of the country. Officials said during
this period an estimated 55,000 persons have been killed. 
</P>
