<HEADLINE> Red Tide Returns to Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Red tide, which gradually ebbed
last week, struck back again yesterday in the waters of the
south China's Guangdong province.
</P>
<P>
It was found in a 100-sq. km area of the waters in western
Shenzhen Special Economic Zone, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Some shellfish have been affected by the red tide, the paper
said, adding that no widespread damages have been reported so far.
</P>
<P>
Now oceanographers are tightening and expanding their
examinations along the coastal areas to help prevent and control
the red tide.
</P>
<P>
This year's red tide has already killed more than 400 tons of
fish and caused more than 40 million yuan in direct loss.
</P>
</TEXT>
