<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Good News For Shanghai's Battery-Powered Cyclists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Local battery-powered cyclists
will no longer have to worry about getting their batteries
charged, since a special company is to be set up to help them.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen charging centers and 100 battery banks will be set up
in the city -- battery service every five km on the streets in
urban areas.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Municipal Battery-Powered Bicycle Industry
Development Center announced that these facilities will be managed
by a company soon to be set up, called the Shanghai
Battery-Powered Bicycle Battery Service Co. Ltd., in an effort to
bolster the market for such vehicles.
</P>
<P>
Cyclist will be able to rent batteries from the banks or pay a
fee for having their own batteries charged.
</P>
<P>
There will also be emergency charging stations, at which
batteries can be charged with enough power to enable a bicycle to
go another ten km, by inserting a coin in a slot
</P>
<P>
The local authorities regard battery-powered bicycles as major
substitutes for gasoline-powered scooters and motorcycles, which
pollute the environment badly. The city government plans to reduce
the number of gas-powered bikes by 400,000.
</P>
<P>
Currently, battery-powered bicycles can travel 30-50 km every
charge, while their prices, at 2,000 yuan-5,000 yuan each, are
regarded as reasonable by local residents in this largest
industrial city in the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
