<HEADLINE> Danish Workers Start Strike for More Holidays </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, April 27 (Xinhua)-- About 450,000 Danish workers
started on Monday a strike demanding for more holidays, according
to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The strike, the biggest in 13 years, has stopped many bus
routes in Copenhagen and cancelled all flights of Scandinavian
Airlines System (SAS).
</P>
<P>
Danish Prime Minister Poul Nyrup Rasmussen has urged the parties
to come to terms, saying his government would not intervene
immediately to end the strike. 
