<HEADLINE> Cuba, Canada Vow to Strengthen Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Cuban President Fidel Castro
Monday held talks with visiting Canadian Prime Minister Jean
Chretien and the two leaders vowed to strengthen cooperation and
continue building common ground on international issues.
</P>
<P>
Chretien, who arrived here on Sunday for a three-day visit,
pledged that his visit is aimed to build dialogue and
comprehension links, as part of a constructive policy.
</P>
