<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- China is in favor of holding a U.N.
Millennium Summit in 2000, Deputy Chinese Permanent Representative
to the U.N. Shen Guofang said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the plenary session on U.N. reforms, Shen said the
United Nations should have an opportunity to look back at the past
55 years and envisage its future task and direction of development
for it to meet the challenges of the next century. (UN-Millennium
Summit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. Senate began on Monday a debate on the
expansion of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), which
will lead a final vote on the measure to add Poland, Hungary and
the Czech Republic to the alliance.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a Senate press briefing, Defense Secretary William
Cohen sought to dismiss "apocalyptic suggestions" that expanding
NATO to include the three former Soviet bloc nations would poison
relations with Moscow, as charged by opponents. (US-NATO-Senate)
</P>
