lost," Clinton said at a White House ceremony marking Israel's
50th anniversary of statehood. (US-Israel-Clinton)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- The number of deaths among Iraq's children and
elderly has increased appallingly due to the U.N. sanctions
imposed since its invasion of Kuwait in 1990, the latest
statistics showed.
</P>
<P>
According to Iraq's health ministry, 5,617 Iraqi children died
in March, compared with only 362 in the same month of 1989 before
the economic sanctions were put into place.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the figures showed, 2,215 old people in Iraq died in
March, up from 407 nine year earlier. (Iraq-Sanctions-Deaths)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Sinn Fein leader Gerry Adams Monday called for more
progress on the "demilitarization" of Northern Ireland in the wake
of the peace agreement struck two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
After meeting with British Prime Minister Tony Blair in Downing
Street for 90 minutes, Adams also called for replacement of the
Royal Ulster Constabulary, the province's Protestant-dominated
police force, by a "proper policing service."
</P>
<P>
But he said too much haste in the disarming of the Irish
Republican Army (IRA) and other guerrilla groups was not
realistic. (UK-N.Irish-Adams)
</P>
<P>
