<HEADLINE> Assassination of Archbishop in Guatemala Confirmed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Guatemalan police Monday
confirmed the assassination of Juan Gerardi, the substitute
archbishop of Guatemala, on Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
A police report said Gerardi, 72, also general
coordinator of the human rights office of the archbishopric
(ODHA), was shot dead by unidentified gunmen in the San
Sebastian church, his residence in the Guatemala City.
</P>
<P>
The body of Gerardi was discovered almost two hours after the
attack and the church is located only three blocks away from the
presidential house and the national palace.
</P>
<P>
Director of the civil national police, Angel Conte and general
attorney, Hector Perez, also confirmed the murder.
</P>
<P>
Last Thursday, Gerardi made public a document against the
atrocities perpetrated during the 36-year civil war. The document
said that in the bloody conflict, more than 55,000 persons were
killed.
</P>
<P>
ODHA director Ronalth Ochaeta said Gerardi's killing was
aimed at undermining a ceasefire agreement which was signed on
December 29, 1996 between the government and the "guerillas".
</P>
</TEXT>
