<HEADLINE> Red Cross Playing Bigger Role in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The two-year-old Red Cross Society
of the Tibet Autonomous Region is playing an increasingly bigger
role in disaster-relief and poverty-eradication there, according
to official sources.
</P>
<P>
Parts of Tibet have been hit by severe snowstorms since last
August, and so far the Red Cross Society of Tibet has received
relief goods worth some four million yuan from red cross societies
in the rest of the country, as well as foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
The society has distributed the donated food, fuel, clothing,
quilts and medicines to the affected areas in line with
international practice, according to Zhong Yin, president of the
Regional Red Cross Society.
</P>
<P>
He said that Tibet is economically backward and over 200,000
Tibetans still live below the poverty line. To bring relief to the
poor is one of the major tasks of the society, he said.
</P>
<P>
With the help of the China Red Cross Society and overseas
groups, the Tibetan society has conducted many activities in the
poor areas, such as holding training courses for medical personnel
and drivers, and sending medical teams to remote villages,
according to Zhong.
</P>
<P>
He asked domestic and overseas groups and individuals to
support his organization, saying that the society wants to
cooperate with them without any political preconditions
whatsoever.  
</P>
</TEXT>
