<HEADLINE> OAS Chief Asks to Build a Fresh, Renewed OAS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Cesar Gaviria, Secretary
General of the Organization of American States (OAS), asked
Monday to build a "fresh and renewed" OAS.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the seminar "Present and Future of OAS" held
at the Mexican Chancery, Gaviria said he was optimistic with the
possibility of creating an integrated, peaceful and democratic
America.
</P>
<P>
The hemispherical relations have changed and a possibility to
build a renewed global order is open after the end of the Cold
War, he said.
</P>
<P>
He urged the American countries to respect the basic rights of
migrating people and ethnic minorities and to intensify efforts in
order to strengthen justice systems and judicial organs.
</P>
<P>
The secretary general emphasized that additional efforts should
be made by American countries for joint diplomatic actions,
economical cooperation, conflict prevention and fruitful exchange
of experiences to build a new era of the Americas.
</P>
