<HEADLINE> Local Companies to Run Express Mail Services in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Three local Myanmar private
companies are planning to join in running international express
postal services following the first launching of this kind of
services in the form of joint venture between the country's posts
and telecommunications authority and a Netherlandish company,
official newspaper the New Light of Myanmar reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The state-run Myanmar Posts and Telecommunications (MPT) and
the DHL Worldwide Express BV of the Netherland established the
foremost joint venture in the country, operating international
express mail services since April 1997.
</P>
<P>
The companies to join the business are Overseas Courier
Service, Indo-China Express and Wah Wah Co, the report said.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the MPT has also informed other
companies in the country to cease their engagement in this service
if they fail to conduct the business in line with the MPT
principles.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar's posts and telecommunications services are run by the
government as the sole agent. However, a number of foreign
companies have been involved in the installation of other
telecommunications system in the country such as radio-telephones
on contracts in recent years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
