<HEADLINE> Shanghai German Center For Industry, Trade Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The construction of the Shanghai
German Center For Industry and Trade started on Sunday in the
Zhangjiang Hi-Tech Park, in the Pudong New Area in this east China
metropolis.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the commencement ceremony, Germany's Economics
Minister G. Rexrodt said that the project shows his country's
confidence in China's future economic development.
</P>
<P>
More small and medium-sized German firms are expected to invest
in China in the future, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Bayerische Landesbank of Germany will invest 100 million DM
in the project, which is backed by the German government, according
to German sources.
</P>
<P>
The project, which covers 30,000 sq m and is scheduled to be
completed by 2000, includes office buildings, small industrial
workshops, exhibition halls, restaurants and hotels.
</P>
<P>
It is designed to help German companies to enter the Chinese
market by providing market studies, legal consultation, and
translation and postal services.
</P>
<P>
The project has been initiated on the basis of a survey among
5,000 small and medium-sized companies in Germany.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, the bank opened a smaller center for the same purpose
at Tongji University here, but it was found to be too small to
meet the growing needs, the sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
