<HEADLINE> New Rapid Deployment Forces Created in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Greek Defense Minister Akis
Tsohatzopoulos announced Monday that Greece had at the beginning
of this month created a new rapid deployment force within the
Greek armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Announcing this while visiting the base of the rapid deployment
force in Veria, northern Greece, Tsohatzopoulos said that the
Greek government decided 14 months ago to create the second army
corps which was ready to deploy and operate as a unit in any part
of the country, according to the semi-official Athens News Agency
(ANA) Monday.
