<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Supports Millennium Summit Idea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 27 (Xinhua) -- China is in favor of
holding a U.N. Millennium Summit in 2000, Deputy Chinese Permanent
Representative to the U.N. Shen Guofang said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the plenary session on U.N. reforms, Shen said the
United Nations should have an opportunity to look back at the past
55 years and envisage its future task and direction of development
for it to meet the challenges of the next century.
</P>
<P>
He proposed that the General Assembly set up an open-ended
preparatory committee to determine the agenda for the summit.
</P>
<P>
The summit idea was raised by U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan
in his latest report to the General Assembly to elaborate his U.N.
reform plans.
</P>
<P>
Such a summit may articulate a vision for the U.N. in the new
century and propose system-wide institutional adaptations enabling
the world body to act on the vision, Annan said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
